title: Senior Spotlight: Ashton Teeter
text: Ed O'Brien PaPreps.com Recruiting Analyst Ashton Teeter is a 6'3", 185 pound, wide receiver from Plum High School. Teeter was slated to appear at the PA PREPS All-State Camp back in March but suffered an injury that prevented him from attending the event. Teeter attended several prospect camps over the summer that included a stop at Ohio State. It was at the Ohio State prospect camp that Teeter recorded a 40-yard dash time in the 4.4 range. Teeter has had a productive season so far through five games. Teeter has caught a total of 17 passes for 377 yards (22.2 yards per catch) and four touchdowns. From a recruiting standpoint, Teeter does not have an offer at this time. Teeter is a little bit under the radar from a recruitment standpoint, but with his height, pass-catching ability and speed to separate from defenders down the field, he should start to get more notice.
